questions.question:
Consider the C struct defined below:
struct data {
    int marks[100];
    char grade;
    int cnumber;
};
struct data student;
The base address of student is available in register R1. The field student.grade can be accessed efficiently using:

A. Post-increment addressing mode, with (R1) as the effective address
B. Pre-decrement addressing mode, with (R1) as the effective address
C. Register direct addressing mode, with R1 as the effective address
D. Index addressing mode, with X as an offset represented in 2's complement 16-bit representation
